Think of Separation of Concerns (SoC) as organizing responsibility so that each part of your system has exactly one reason to exist and one reason to change.

If DRY is about not repeating yourself, SoC is about not mixing responsibilities.

example :
class UserService {
    validateUser();
    saveUser();
    logUser();
    sendEmail();
    formatResponse();
}

this UserService is a god class and it knows too much
UserValidator
UserRepository
EmailService
UserService (orchestrates) - the service coordinates with other responsibilities and do not do anything by itself


